Lumpy skin disease [LSD], Israel
--------------------------------
Information received on 20 Aug 2012 from Dr Nadav Galon, Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Bet Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 1
Start date: 01 Jul 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event:27 Jul 2012
Report date 20 Aug 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 20 Aug 2012
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence November 2007
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country
Related reports: Immediate notification, 27 Jul 2012

New outbreaks
- Outbreak 1 (Shamir) Shamir, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 03 Aug 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 1050/ 6/ 1/ 0/ 0
Affected Population:
a. Free ranging herd - 400 heads. Morbidity: 4 (1.0 percent); mortality: 1.
b. Fattening enclosure - 650 heads. Morbidity: 2 (0.3 percent). No mortality.

- Outbreak 2 (Kefar Szold) Kefar Szold, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak 12 Jul 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 528/ 104/ 3/ 0/ 0
Affected Population:
a. Herd 1 - 250 heads, 60 cases, 3 deaths (morbidity 24 percent).
b. Herd 2 - 250 heads, 40 cases, no deaths (morbidity 16 percent).
c. Breeding bulls - morbidity 4/28 (14 percent), no deaths.

- Outbreak 3 (Qela) Qela, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 08 Aug 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 150/ 45/ 4/ 0/ 0
Affected Population: Free ranging herds:
a. Herd 1 - 60 heads. Morbidity 20 (33 percent). 2 deaths.
b. Herd 2 - 90 heads. Morbidity 25 (28 percent). 2 deaths.

- Outbreak 4 (Ein Qiniyye) Ein Qiniyye, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jul 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 100/ 17/ 0/ 0/ 0
Affected Population: 2 herds of 50 dams were found affected.
In one herd the morbidity is 24 percent and in the second herd - 10 percent.

- Outbreak 5 (Lahavot Habashan) Lahavot Habashan, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 07 Aug 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 200/ 5/ 0/ 0/ 0
Affected Population: Free ranging herd in the Golan heights.

- Outbreak 6 (Birkat Man) Birkat Man, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 10 Jul 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 450/ 42/ 2/ 0/ 0
Affected Population: 7 herds roam in the area. In 2 of them the morbidity is 22 percent. In the others 0-2 percent show clinical signs.

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 6
Total animals affected:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 2478/ 219/ 10/ 0/ 0

Outbreak statistics:
Species/ Apparent morbidity rate/ Apparent mortality rate/ Apparent case fatality rate/ Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle/ 8.84 percent/ 0.40 percent/ 4.57 percent/ 0.40 percent

* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors.

Epidemiological comments: Before this event the disease was detected only in the south of Israel in 1989, 2006 and 2007.
The herds are located in the north of the country, near the Syrian and Lebanese borders. All the cases are concentrated in the Golan heights and the upper Galilee. Stomoxis flies have been seen in the area.

Control measures
Measures applied: Control of arthropods, Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, Screening, Dipping and/or Spraying, Modified stamping out.
Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s):
Administrative division/ Species/ Total Vaccinated/ Details
Hazafon/ Cattle/ 35 000/ Sheep pox vaccine

Measures to be applied: No other measures

